overview: The user initiated a request for a comprehensive review of their sleep
  questionnaire application, which included a detailed specification and a
  Statement of Work. The agent performed an in-depth analysis of the existing
  codebase, comparing it against the provided requirements. This review
  highlighted several gaps and missing features, which the agent then organized
  into a prioritized action plan. Upon user approval of the plan, the agent
  began implementation. The first completed task involved integrating a 1-10
  severity scale for tiredness interference into the questionnaire. This
  enhancement included dynamic safety warnings for high severity scores, which
  are displayed both within the questionnaire itself and in the generated PDF
  report. The implementation required modifications across multiple files,
  including type definitions, validation schemas, UI components, and report
  generation logic, ensuring the application now captures and communicates
  critical safety information related to user-reported tiredness.
